  "instructions": {
    "instructions_text": "Each question below contains has a snippet from a song that went on to have a well-known cover version by a different artist. We want the name of the *artist that released the cover version*, _not_ the artist performing the recorded sample.\nNote that some songs have inspired multiple well-known covers, so pay attention to the *year* of the cover given in the question which sould narrow it down to a single cover.\n\nFor example, if the question states 'Original: 1974; Cover: 1992.' and had this clip:",
    "sample_audiofile": "/Users/mcmenamin/Repos/sundries/ll_covers/data/trimmed/35a04d7d5f77_42707_45942.mp3",
    "post_sample_text": "You should listen to that sample and figure out that it is the song _I Will Always Love You_ (originally released by Dolly Parton in 1974). In 1992, it was covered in by Whitney Houston. So the correct answer should be \"Whitney Houston\".\n\n\nOther caveats/comments:\n* I need to whittle this down to a smaller set, so I've got a feedback box for each question. Let me know if the snippet i selected wasnt good (too hard/too easy), the cover wasn't sufficiently famous that you think people would know it, or whether if any of them are particulary interesting and that i should be sure to include it.\n* For the purposes of this test, some songs have multiple snippets that I'm testing out but the real version will just have one. If you have opinions on which candidates to use, let me know in the feedback.\n* I've tried to avoid picking song clips that include the name of the song, but I'm not sure if that's important seeing that the answer is the *artist* and not the song. In some cases it'd make it too easy, but I'm not sure if I've made things needlessly hard by imposing that rule\n* There are some duplicate artists in the originals and for answers. I'll make sure to avoid that in the final question set"
  },
